  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into fries</p><p>Add the <strong>fries</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and your <strong>dried oregano</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until crisp – these are your <strong>herby fries</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1679394616525-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1679394616525-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1679394616525-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1679394616525-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1679394616525-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Slice <strong>half</strong> your <strong>cucumber[s]</strong> into discs</p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining cucumber</strong> in half lengthways, scrape out the inner seeds with a teaspoon and discard</p><p>Grate the <strong>deseeded cucumber</strong> and squeeze out any excess water</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1679394624890-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1679394624890-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1679394624890-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1679394624890-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1679394624890-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Strip your <strong>mint</strong> <strong>leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Add the <strong>grated cucumber</strong> to a bowl with <strong>half </strong>the<strong> chopped garlic </strong>(not a big garlic fan? Try using less!), <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped mint</strong> (save the rest for garnish!), your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>tzatziki</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
